This paper deals with optimization of interference networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses combinatorial optimization and graph theory concepts, which are relevant to network optimization (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the parallel interference networks, which is a subfield of network optimization (cs.SI). The paper also discusses matching problems, which is a subfield of combinatorial optimization (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the deterministic model of interference networks, which is a subfield of distributed computing (cs.DC).
